name: Boss
description: He ate part of a belt and needed surgery to remove it. Unsure why they'd make something you can't eat look like a giant piece of bacon. Fair point. We covered his medical costs and he's feeling much better.

name: Kirby
description: His engine has started and his ears have been deployed. Please puppare for takeoff.

name: Cohen
description: He takes his health very seriously. Started flossing when he was just a puppy. Dentists adore him, and @JustFoodForDogs is proud to feed him.

name: Tank
description: He limped over to journalist @OzKaterji on a street full of destroyed armored vehicles in Bucha, Ukraine. He was alone and scared, but happy to follow a friendly voice. He was brave at the vet and is finally sleeping while the search for his people continues.

name: Penelopii
description: She just discovered trampolines. Why did no one tell her about this?

name: Bongo
description: He unlocked the multiverse. It was way easier than he thought it would be.

name: Scout
description: She recently had a stroke and lost her ability to walk. She was rushed to the vet and soon diagnosed with Immune Mediated Hemolytic Anemia. She was given a toy and a “good girl” bandage. We’ve paid for the rest of her vet bills and she’s improving every day.

name: Herbert
description: Today he was officially named the longest wiener dog in the world. He’s nearly 3 feet in length, a full foot longer than your average dachshund.

name: Kona
description: She's just so grateful that she found her forever human. Can't believe she gets to spend every day with her best friend.

name: Oliver
description: He wanted you to have these flowers. Picked them out himself. Hopes they’re your favorite color.

name: Moose
description: Watch this. He can make his ears disappear. It's a great party trick. Also his only one.

name: Lou
description: He's at his first vet visit. Waiting for test results to see if he's a good boy. Feeling confident. He studied hard for this.

name: rate dogs
description: This is obviously a duck. This particular duck has @Trupanion, so he only has to worry about one bill. Regardless, please only send dogs. Thank you...

name: Maggie
description: She got sent home from the amusement park. Was told she wasn't tall enough to ride any of the rides. Getting a second opinion.

name: rate dogs
description: This is a mythical wizard. Clearly full of infinite wisdom, but please only send dogs. Thank you...

name: Fezco
description: He was abandoned by his previous owners for being “gay” after he humped another male dog. This week he was adopted by Steve Nichols and his husband, John Winn. The couple has since renamed him Oscar, after Oscar Wilde.

name: Maggie
description: She had happy tail syndrome. She wagged so passionately and so often that her tail would bonk into things, causing bleeding and infection. She was in pain, and the best course of action was amputation. We paid for her surgery and she’s doing so much better.

name: Sarah
description: She has neurological damage that makes it hard for her to stay balanced. Doesn't let that stop her from dancing in the snow.

name: Walter
description: He always asks if he can drive. Can't believe you finally said yes.

name: unny, guys
description: Why would you send in a photo without a dog in it? This is downright disrespectful. We only rate dogs. Thank you...

name: Rocco
description: He's doing his best.

name: Bam Bam
description: He was a little scared on his first plane ride. Felt a lot better after getting a hug from the flight attendant.

name: Lil Hobbs
description: He recently joined a water aerobics class. Likes the water. Not so sure about the aerobics.

name: Benny
description: He got into a heated argument with his lobster toy. Didn't like the way it was talking back to him, so he ate its squeaker. He needed surgery to remove it, so I'd say the lobster won. We covered his medical bills and he's doing better now.

name: rate dogs
description: This is a Cozy Cashmere Caterpillar. They're typically pretty aggressive so please be careful. Remember to only send dogs. Thank you...

name: Meatball
description: He's going home for the very first time. So excited to have a human of his own. Thinking about what he's going to call you. Maybe Bob.

name: Dottie
description: She had spinal compression as a puppy that left her almost unable to walk. Her human turned to @Trupanion for help, and they paid for the vast majority of her $13,000 medical bills. Dottie is proud to report she’s made a full recovery.

name: Odzi
description: He wanted to try ding-dong ditching. Didn't quite catch how the last part works. Would love for you to let him in so he can say hi.

name: Gus
description: And these are his four favorite teeth. Just brushed them this morning. You can even smell his breath if you want.

name: Ozzy
description: He ate one of his chew toys and it had to be surgically removed. He's a little embarrassed and doesn't want to comment on the situation at this time. We've covered the cost of his medical care and he is doing much better now.

name: Horton
description: He's been doing yoga for months. Would like to share that he can finally touch his toes.

name: Buford
description: He’s a proud member of our @JustFoodForDogs Supper Club. Was hoping the food would make his legs grow but it only worked on his ears. Still

name: Muffin
description: She didn’t want to alarm you but she is in fact floating away. Really appreciates the assistance.

name: the very rare Fluffy Rottweiler
description: First sighting in decades. Truly an honor to stumble across.

name: Piggy
description: She noticed you didn't finish your sandwich. Wonders what might happen to the rest of it. Perhaps it could be given to someone. Maybe a good girl.

name: Ruby
description: She was not tall enough to go on the Ferris wheel but her human made sure she got the full amusement park experience anyway.

name: Marv
description: And this is Marv's puppeller hat. He thought it would make him fly. Definitely false advertising.

name: Thor
description: He ate his bed. Like, so much of it he needed surgery to remove it all. Unsure why the inside looks like cotton candy if you can't eat it. We've covered the cost of his medical care. He's feeling much better.

name: Silo
description: He’s working on his entrances. They’re a little aggressive at the moment. Still

name: Vixen
description: He really likes bananas. Steals them when he thinks nobody's watching.

name: a covert secret agent
description: Can infiltrate any room completely undetected. Usually disguised as a teddy bear.

name: Ronan
description: He sneezed so hard his ears flipped inside out. Luckily, another sneeze flipped them back. For the things a second sneeze can’t fix, he has @Trupanion.

name: Rufus
description: Every time he's a good boy, he gets a new toy. As you can see, this happens often.

name: Sture
description: He can't believe you brought up his paw wrinkles. That's the one thing he's sensitive about.

name: Donut
description: He wanted to pop out and say hi. Wondering where your personal chauffeur is. Said you can borrow his, if you'd like.

name: Jeffrey
description: He's being held so he doesn't fly away.

name: Scottie
description: He's so excited about his new collar. It's a little big for him right now, but he heard he'll grow into it.

name: Roxie
description: Her little brother Ziggy got loose and Roxie ran after him. In classic older sibling fashion, she was the one who was hit by a car. We covered the cost of her medical care and she's feeling much better. Only a little annoyed with Ziggy.

name: Ozzy
description: He is so sneaky. If you see him, it's already too late.

name: Dotty
description: There was a small miscommunication about what making snow angels meant. Modeled it after herself.

name: Gamja and Chip
description: Chip’s new to the family, so Gamja is showing him how to play. Core memory achieved.

name: Albie
description: He understands that some people have bad angles but he simply can't relate.

name: Aja
description: She was just told she's a good girl. Suspicions confirmed.

name: Lukka
description: He would like you to drive him to the park now please. Just got @Trupanion so he is ready for whatever’s thrown his way.

name: Charlie
description: He has literal heart-eyes.

name: Eddie and Stan
description: They're the stars of @budweiserusa's Super Bowl commercial. They've been best friends for years and finally caught their big break together. They can’t wait for you to see it.

name: a pineapple
description: We only rate dogs. It's one thing to send us other animals, but sending us a plant is purely uncivilized. Please send dogs... thank you.

name: Ollie
description: He noticed his human drove past the turn for the dog park. Jumped over his protective seat barrier to try to correct them. Ended up falling to the floor and breaking his knee. We paid for his medical expenses and he'll be back at the park in no time.

name: Sherio
description: He helps rescue feral kittens, but right now he’s also fighting cancer. He has his fifth surgery in 11 months coming up to try and slow its spread. The medical bills have been overwhelming, but you can help him with them below.

name: Honey
description: She wants you to spot the difference between these two pics. It’s very subtle so please take your time.

name: Chester and Chelsea
description: Chelsea's love language is physical touch. Chester's is words of affirmation but he does not mind the cuddles because quality time works for him too. Both

name: Rome and Milan
description: They're not sure how you tricked them into this bath, but they want to remind you that you are outnumbered.

name: Thomas
description: He won @notonemorevet’s Cutest Pet Contest, which helped raise over $10,000 for mental health resources to support veterinarians in crisis. He usually doesn’t like to show off but this was for a good cause.

name: Vader
description: He is currently in the snowball fight of the century out there. Requesting back-pup. Really needs someone with opposable thumbs.

name: Rocky
description: He’s been promoted from good boy to best man. Understands what a big deal this is. Taking his duties very seriously.

name: Buddy
description: He found a very tasty looking rock outside. Swallowed it without hesitation. Unfortunately, it couldn't stay in his tummy and had to be surgically removed. We covered the remaining costs of his care, and he agrees that nothing about this experience… rocked.

name: Apple
description: The best part of her day is hearing about yours. Hopes it went well but it’s ok if it didn't. She's not going anywhere.

name: Apollo
description: He was just wondering if- omg… 2319! WE HAVE A 2319! EVERYBODY DOWN. PUPPARE FOR DECONTAMINATION.

name: Scooter
description: She loves to go camping as long as you make sure she is very cozy.

name: Kato
description: He somehow swallowed an entire roll of gauze and needed emergency surgery to remove it. We’ve covered the cost of his medical care so far. He still hasn’t been able to come home, so please join us in wishing him well.

name: Flynn
description: He is just taking a little dip. That’s what he likes to do, so that is what he does.

name: Wrigley
description: According to his data, we are on the verge of a stick shortage. He’s not taking any chances.

name: Indy
description: You don’t need to tell him his pajamas are cute, he is already aware. They also help his allergies. @Trupanion covers his medication and the PJs cover his floof.

name: Lola
description: She really misses her older sister.

name: uys? We only rate dogs
description: This is a Fluffy Flower Mouse. One of the largest we’ve ever seen. Please send in dogs only. Thank you…

name: Nala
description: She spent an entire day practicing her zoomies and was excited to show her dad how fast she can go when he got home from work. Accidentally zoomed right into the street and was hit by a car. We covered the cost of her care and wish her a speedy recovery.

name: Dutch
description: He’s a dentist therapy dog. He’ll rest in your lap and cuddle you while you’re there.

name: ner @JustFoodForDogs donated hundreds of cases of food to shelters and rescues across LA last weekend! This is Bella from Paws For Life K9
description: She was very appreciative.

name: Maci
description: She heard you’ve been petting other dogs. Wants you to explain yourself. Anything you have to say can be said in front of her sock monkey.

name: Bowser
description: He’s the designated baby bouncer for today. Doesn’t mind the responsibility because he’s quite good at it.

name: Moo
description: He’s still getting the hang of things, just in general.

name: Buffy
description: She managed to steal a whole bottle of vitamin D3 off the counter. Thought it would make her big and strong but it only made her need an overnight stay at the vet. We’ve paid for her care and told her we already think she’s big and strong.

name: Theo
description: He had a severe upper respiratory infection as a puppy. @Trupanion preapproved his treatment, and he got the medical care he needed right away. Prefers to worry about his choice of bow tie, not his vet bills.

name: Rocky
description: He gets a little wild when his humans have friends over, so they distract him with squirrel videos.

name: Sabre
description: He recently turned 14 and can no longer walk long distances, but he still loves the beach, so his humans made him a chariot.

name: Sully
description: He had a misunderstanding with the oak tree next door. Thought all the acorns it was dropping were for him. Ate a toxic amount and needed surgery to empty his stomach. We’ve covered the cost of his care and suggest he reevaluates his friendship with the tree.

name: Lapsha
description: She’s wondering if these photos make her nose look big. If you could take a peek and get back to her that'd be great.

name: Buddy
description: He ran into a glass door once. Now he's h*ckin skeptical.

name: Tinsley
description: She was in a car accident with her humans last night. She escaped the wreckage, got the attention of police, and led them all the way back to the site of the crash. Her humans are being treated and expected to survive. Tinsley is awarded our very rare…

name: Millie and Wilbur
description: They've always flirted with each other on walks. Today they finally booped snoots. A big step. Both

name: Chloe
description: You all fully funded her GoFundMe campaign earlier this year. She received the surgery she needed and got to spend 8 more happy months with her family—long enough to be the flower girl at her humans’ wedding, all thanks to you.

name: George
description: He did not steal the gingerbread house. This line of questioning is inappropriate without counsel present.

name: Frodo
description: He was the last of 48 survivors rescued from Michael Vick’s dogfighting operation in 2007. He passed away over the weekend at the age of 15, surrounded by so much love. He and the rest of his very brave friends helped change animal welfare forever.

name: Jamesy
description: He gives a single tender kiss to every other pup he sees on his walk. Very kind of him.

name: Appa
description: It’s his first time in the snow. Pretty sure he caught every flake.

name: Zena
description: She definitely mentioned she did not want a bath. You must’ve not heard her.

name: Barron and his son, Carlos
description: Carlos just came home from college after barely surviving finals. Barron missed him a whole bunch and will not leave him alone. Both

name: Ruckus
description: His humans don’t have kids, so they take him to see the lights every year. He absolutely loves it.

name: Luna
description: She jumped the fence in her yard while chasing a squirrel and was hit by a car. We covered the rest of her medical bills and she’s doing much better now. We tried contacting the squirrel, because they are obviously liable, but they didn’t return our emails.

name: Moose
description: He’s wondering where Santa’s reindeer tryouts are. Knows he has what it takes.

name: Pizza Dog
description: He’s the very good boy in Marvel Studios’ Hawkeye. Thinks his nickname is fitting but would have also accepted “Pupperoni.”

name: Libby
description: She had a scab on her nose and when it healed, it left a perfect pink heart. A target for your smooches, if you will.

name: Howdy
description: He’s the new sheriff. I know he’s not like super intimidating but please respect his authority. He gets grumpy if you don’t.

name: Buckaroo
description: He is 12 years old and sometimes he gets sore. Warm baths always help him feel better. His dad holds his pillow and his brothers come by for emotional support.

name: Clark
description: She wanted to play hide and seek with a sock. Decided swallowing it was an easy win, but her vet cheated and found it using an x-ray machine. We covered the cost of her surgery to get it out, and hope she picks a different hiding place next time.

name: Teddy
description: He’s found several clues that indicate there’s a good boy around here somewhere. Maybe you’ve seen him.

name: Haru
description: She is just now waking from her food coma. It lasted all weekend. A few more minutes couldn’t hurt though.

name: Butchy
description: He really enjoys his swimming time. No thoughts just peace and little paw paddles.

name: Baxter
description: He’s going to need a lot of attention today. He can just tell.

name: Doogus
description: We were told someone laughed at his pj’s, so now he needs your help to feel better.

name: Stella
description: Despite her age, she still tippy taps with the best of them.

name: Wilson
description: He won last year’s Pupweiser contest! Find his face on Budweiser cans in store right now. It was so much fun we’re doing it again! Post a pic of your pup using #pupweisercontest and tag @budweiserusa for a chance to be the face of their next holiday can.

name: Chevy
description: He doesn’t mind the colder weather because he gets to wear his hoodie. It’s very cozy.

name: Vinny
description: He’s using his disappearing powers. Not sure who this lady is talking to.

name: Juniper
description: Because of daylight savings, she had to play fetch in the dark. The light was low and the stakes were high. She jumped for her ball, landed awkwardly and broke her leg. We’ve paid for her surgery and support her movement to end daylight savings for good.

name: Stork
description:
She’s helping me give away a set of custom wedges with @CallawayGolf! We’ll even put a pic of your dog on the third one ⛳️🐾

To enter, retweet this post & follow @puppiesandgolf, a nonprofit serving dogs and shelters in need.

name: Titus and Roo
description: Titus doesn’t stop drooling so Roo got a raincoat for when they hang out. It seems dramatic but it’s not.

name: y? We only rate dogs
description: This is a velociraptor. She won’t hurt you she is just startled. Please send dogs only. Thank you…

name: Louie
description: He’s been catching flights while you’ve been catching feelings.

name: Edgar
description: He’s in training to be a service dog for his human. Did a very good job yesterday.

name: Nova
description: She’s an amateur bandana model trying to break into the professional scene. Has @Trupanion so very few things can come between her and the runway.

name: Apollo
description: He escaped his yard and was shot by an unknown neighbor. A piece of the bullet punctured his bladder and he needed surgery to remove it. We’ve paid for the remaining cost of all his medical care. He's a little annoyed this happened but is doing much better.

name: Sierra
description: Last week she woke up vomiting. The emergency vet discovered her intestine had flipped inside out. Immediate surgery to remove part of it was necessary to save her life. You can help Sierra with her recovery by clicking below.

name: Jake and Izzy
description: They are having a yawning duel. And the first shot has been fired. Both

name: Kabosu
description: She just turned 16 years old. She’s a rescue Shiba Inu who changed the world with an impromptu photoshoot back in 2010. Her slightly raised eyebrows and crossed paws remain one the greatest reaction images of all time.

name: Saoirse
description: She was on track to become one of the best snowflake collectors of her generation. Sadly, she developed hip dysplasia and had to take a break to fix it. @Trupanion helped cover those medical bills, and now she’s once again coming for the throne.

name: Coach
description: She overheard you say something about the neighbor being a good girl. Just checking if that was about her.

name: Barley
description: He’s a Beanie Baby for Halloween. Missing a leg so his stuffing was coming out.

name: Gunner
description: He fell down the stairs. Not sure who put them there or why elevation changes are necessary in the first place. We paid for his surgery to fix his broken leg, and he has his big t-rex to comfort him.

name: Kevin
description: It’s suspected he was abused in his prior home. He arrived at a shelter with an injured knee and torn ligaments in both back legs. He’s safe and loved now, but needs a few operations to live a pain-free life. You can help him below.

name: Atlas
description: He just got his braces off. Wanted to show everyone his new smile.

name: Sadie and Niki
description: They have to be touching at all times. Doesn't matter how.

name: Chad
description: He’s a very good boy. Likes being held. Fluffy and portable. Weird bark but that’s okay.

name: Cooper
description: He built the picket fence himself. Needed a break from the rest of the world.

name: Bailey
description: She is a professional barkour athlete. Do not try this at home.

name: Hagar
description: He is watching you watch his favorite movie and wants to make sure you laugh at the funny parts.

name: Ragnar
description: He's on his way to the park. Never been to one before. Put on a bow tie to hopefully make a good first impression.

name: Luna
description: In her defense, that is her bed.

name: Oscar
description: He thinks his toys should stay evenly distributed around the house. Decided to eat part of his toy basket in protest. This gave him a pupset tummy and a lengthy trip to the vet. We’ve covered the cost of his care and agreed his toys can go wherever he wants.

name: is Jade
description: She was tied up in a bag and thrown from the window of a car before being rescued by a passerby. She’s since found her forever home and spends her days cuddling with her best friend, a rainbow narwhal.

name: is Leo
description: He was abandoned by backyard breeders when they realized he was born paralyzed. He was rescued, adopted, and given the fanciest assistive cart ever. He doesn’t know anything’s wrong and you’re not allowed to tell him otherwise.

name: is Haddie
description: She was used as a bait dog for dogfighting. She needed a ton of medical attention when she was rescued, but since her adoption last year, she’s become the “smartest, sweetest, goofiest, most spoiled dog ever.”

name: Frysauce
description: He spent the entire summer crocheting this sweater for you. Only rule is that you have to share it with him.

name: Beau
description: He’s taking a power snoozle before continuing his med school studies. Wears the stethoscope for motivation.

name: Buster
description: His energy can’t be contained. Decided to leap from his human’s arms and lost a fight with gravity. Now he needs orthopedic surgery for his fractured leg. We’ve covered the cost of his pupcoming operation and wish him a swift recovery.

name: Devi
description: She recently lost function of her hind end and needs spinal surgery and months of PT for a chance at full recovery. Her life was very hard before being rescued. She deserves nothing but happiness moving forward. You can help her below.

name: Lilly
description: She just parallel barked. Kindly requests a reward now.

name: Kalua
description: He has a big date tonight. Little nervous about his choice of bow tie, but we don't think he has reason to be.

name: Kiko and Tofu
description: They were walking along the beach when Tofu started floating away. Somebody call someone. Anybody. Please. Both

name: Lujzi
description: She smiles wherever she goes. Learned it usually makes others smile too.

name: rate dogs
description: This is a Patagonian Round Bat. Reacts positively to watermelon, but that's all we know so far. Please send dogs only. Thank you...

name: Jupiter
description: She loves her rope toy but hates the idea of having to go anywhere without it… so she swallowed it. Had to have emergency surgery to remove it. We covered the cost of her care, and both she (and the toy, somehow?) are expected to make a full recovery.

name: Diego
description: He plays Cosmo the telepathic Space Dog in the pupcoming @Marvel Guardians of the Galaxy video game. He was fitted with a high-tech motion capture suit to create all the in-game footage.

name: Bush
description: It was very windy at the beach today but he remained anchored.

name: Wallace
description: You said you brushed your teeth this morning but he checked your toothbrush and it was bone dry.

name: Leon
description: He is very puppared for any inclement weather. Literally nothing could come between him and his walkies.

name: Guinness
description: He thinks his family adopted a kitten just for him.

name: Virgil
description: He accidentally swallowed one of his toys' plastic eyes. Not sure why they make them the tastiest part if he cannot eat them. He's a bit embarrassed, but we've covered the cost of his procedure and he's recovering well.

name: Sheba
description: She has a lymphoma tumor on her neck that is too dangerous to surgically remove. Her best chance at survival is chemotherapy. Without it, she only has a few weeks left. You can help Sheba and her family afford treatment below.

name: Maggie
description: Playing in the snow was her favorite thing in the world, and she got to do it one final time thanks to @SLCOParksandRec. Their staff shaved extra ice, loaded it into bins, and gave it to her family, making Maggie’s last day very very special.

name: Huxley
description: He hopes you had a good day, but if not, he’s conveniently right here and an excellent listener.

name: Sampson
description: He had a serious infection at just 5 weeks old. He survived, but with permanent damage to the left side of his brain. He’s healthy now, but does a few interesting things as a result. One of which, is somersault.

name: Rux
description: He needs everyone to know this is not a phase. This is who he really is.

name: Onyx
description: He fell up the stairs and broke his leg. Wasn’t going fast or anything stairs are just difficult. We’ve covered the cost of his emergency care.

name: Stanze
description: She’s struggling with severe ear infections. They’ve caused facial swelling and paralysis, leading to blindness and trouble breathing. She needs total ear canal ablation surgery as soon as possible and you can help her get it below.

name: Ace
description: He went to his first ever baseball game AND got to try a hot dog. Was excited about both, but a little bit more so for the hot dog.

name: Stanley
description: He is patiently waiting his 30 minutes after eating so he can hop in the pool.

name: Sir Tibbles and Lukas
description: Sir Tibbles has resting grump face, so Lukas gives him spontaneous hugs. It may not look like they work, but they definitely do.

name: Stone
description: He likes to wear socks outside. It's a questionable lifestyle but we support it.

name: Kevin
description: He’s an aspiring astronaut. Always brings his stuffed bear on training missions.

name: Harvey
description: He’s the next Avatar. Mastered all four elements with ease.

name: Teddy
description: He has been on a Himalayan retreat for the past 3 years and requests to be caught up to speed on the state of the world.

name: Mabel
description: She had to have emergency surgery to remove two chunks of a tennis ball from her stomach. Claims she’s never seen that ball before and that doesn’t sound like something she’d do. We’ve covered the cost of her care regardless, and she’s feeling much better.

name: Dixie
description: She’s been having trouble walking and controlling her bladder due to a cancerous mass on her spleen. She underwent surgery to remove it and is waiting on the biopsy. She’s being very brave and you can help her by clicking below.

name: Tony
description: He’s been patiently waiting for hot girl summer to end so he can start his wrinkly potato autumn.

name: Buster and Roscoe
description: They were separated from their humans during Hurricane Ida. Both were reunited this week by @LASPCA. You all raised over $43k for their relief fund, and helped make this possible.

name: Finn
description: He goes door to door asking if anybody has seen the good boy. They have now, of course.
We only rate dogs. This is a Silly Seaside T-Rex. Please evacuate the beach immediately. Thank you…

name: Siri
description: She heard you’re not supposed to go chasing waterfalls. Went anyway and it was lovely. Not sure why they say that.

name: Brixton
description: He’s the captain now. A little embarrassed because he already misunderstood the purpose of the poop deck.

name: Mo
description: He has very long legs, which he uses for exceptional zoomies. Last week he zoomed into the dining room table and broke his leg. We’ve covered the remaining cost of the surgery to fix it. Mo is willing to abide by a household speed limit moving forward.

name: Winston
description: He was born with both an underdeveloped sternum and front arms. He needs a series of chest reconstruction surgeries and he’s growing so fast he needs a new set of wheels every other week. You can help him and his rescuers below.

name: Davey
description: He’s here to pick up your daughter. Will have her home by 9. Not a second later.

name: Reggie
description: He’s wondering if this bus has any stops near the pet store. He’s been saving for a new toy.

name: rate dogs
description: This is clearly a little airplane awaiting clearance for takeoff. Please send dogs only. Thank you…

name: Lola
description: Today she won first place in the “Most Gorgeous Oldie” competition. Always knew she had what it takes but it’s nice to be validated.

name: Sokka
description: Last Saturday night he was hit by a car. The car sped off and Sokka was left with large skin injuries requiring stitches. We’ve covered the remaining cost of his emergency care. He’s doing much better now.

name: Muffin
description: She was rescued in the aftermath of Hurricane Ida by @LASPCA. They’ve been working nonstop to rescue displaced animals and provide vet care to affected communities. They desperately need donations through the link below.

name: Ferris and Luka
description: Once a week they take a hot air balloon ride to the tulip fields. Magical as h*ck.

name: Scooby
description: He's a little concerned he got a treat stuck up his nose. Wondering if you could take a look.

name: O’Malley
description: That is how he sleeps. Doesn’t care what you think about it.

name: Rusty and Coop
description: Rusty’s hugging technique is still aggressive and a little bit overwhelming. Grateful he has a friend to practice on.

name: Walter
description: He just found out you forgot to record his favorite TV show again. Thinks he should get to hold the remote from now on.

name: Max
description: He’s an aspiring landscaper. Believes in doing all the hard work himself. Isn’t afraid to get his paws dirty.

name: Loki
description: She finally joined the retirement club. Planned an elaborate vacation to Hawaii, but decided to bring Hawaii to her instead.

description: They are the mother-daughter duo you need to see today. Both

name: Ezra

description: With the help of @justfoodfordogs, he went from over 170 pounds (certified chonk) to under 140 (healthy agile boy). Wanted to take a moment and thank everyone who believed in him.

description: He would like to discuss bigger bowl options whenever you get a chance. It’s just that this looks ridiculous.

name: Tammy

name: Kona

description: He thought maybe you would like a sunflower this morning. Picked it out all by himself.

name: Rivers
description: So far no one has realized he is not a horse. His plan is going perfectly. Soon he will have all the hay he wants.

name: Kovu
description: He tried to kiss a snake, but it bit him on the tongue. Had to spend a couple expensive days at the hospital on anti-venom treatment. We’ve covered the remaining cost of his care. Please consider getting pet medical insurance. It’s best to be puppared.

name: Jiho
description: He was born with deformities of his front legs. He’s made progress with his mobility under the care of his foster family, but now that he’s old enough, it’s time for surgery to amputate. You can help Jiho by clicking the link below.

name: Betty and Rhett
description: Rhett just wanted ONE toy to play with, but Betty got to them first. She always does this.

name: Mya
description: She’s been learning to sing the Star Wars theme song. Finally got it at the end there.

name: Wrigley
description: He’s steppin out for a bit if you guys need anything. Tired of nobody seeing his fits.

name: Burger
description: He thinks he’s invisible. Would’ve pulled it off if it weren’t for his wiggles.

name: Tonkey
description: She has @trupanion medical insurance. The only thing it hasn’t protected her from over the years... is bath time.

name: Calvin
description: He was the ring bearer for his human’s wedding. Was a little nervous but did a phenomenal job.

name: Kip
description: He was adopted at 10 years old and just turned 14 last month. Lost all his teeth so his tongue just kinda does what it wants. Hopes that’s okay.

name: Jay
description: He thought he would grow into his ears, but they also kept growing. Not sure what to do now.

name: Peyton
description: She’s available for adoption through @LostOurHome in Tempe, Arizona. She’s a super smiley girl who does well with other pups! And you can invite her to be a part of your family by clicking the link below.

name: Snowelle
description: She’s our Canadian pup of the day! Available through @ManitobaMutts. Would like to know when it’s going to be her turn to play Mario Brothers. You can adopt Snowelle by clicking the link below.

name: Mint
description: She’s adoptable from @Muttville Senior Dog Rescue in San Fransisco. She holds the world record for tinniest crossed paws and would love a home to call her own. You can give her one by clicking below.

name: Mogwai
description: She’s been with @kcpetproject since last June. Her foster home discovered she really likes pajamas, so all potential adopters please jot that down. You can learn all about Mogwai by clicking the link below.

name: Beans
description: He’s available for adoption through @doggoneseattle. He asked if showing a little tongue would increase his chances of finding a home, and we said yes tbh it probably will. You can apply to adopt Beans below.

name: Aubrey
description: She’s searching for her perfect someone with the help of Companion Animal Alliance in Baton Rouge, Louisiana. I’m told she’s the “loneliest heart in the shelter” and you can apply to fix that and be her human below.

name: Champ
description: He’s pup for adoption through Wags and Walks in Nashville. His ideal human likes snuggling and that’s a nonnegotiable. He does well will other pups and you can apply to adopt him below.

name: Queenie
description: She came to @BuffaloCARES back in November with her four puppies. All her pups have found loving homes, and now it’s her turn. You can apply to adopt Queenie by clicking below.

name: Sheba, an Australian Shepherd mix available through @heavencanwaitlv in Las Vegas
description: She needs a patient human who will continue her training. Also, she can make her ears disappear. You can learn more about her below.

name: Daenerys
description: She’s currently available through @AustinDogRescue. She loves sunshine and sprinklers, and yes, she does have a few dragon friends she’ll introduce you to if you’re lucky. You can apply to adopt Dany below.

name: Doc
description: He wants to be a beekeeper. Definitely didn’t get stuck going through the trash.

name: Stan
description: He’s very serious about you having a good day. Any pawblems just send them his way. He’ll take care of it.

name: Lola
description: She was recently diagnosed with bone cancer in her leg. Thankfully, it hadn’t spread far and an amputation saved her. We’ve covered the remaining cost of her care. Please consider getting pet health insurance. It’s best to be puppared.

name: Shanel
description: She has lymphoma cancer. Her chemotherapy is working great, but she’s only halfway through her treatments and cannot afford to complete them. Her little sister Sweda really wants her to beat this, and you can help her do it below.

name: Sky
description: He hopes you had a good Wednesday. If not, maybe his Sid the Sloth impression will help.

name: Sugar and Ellie
description: Sugar was a WWE superstar in a past life, and Ellie has learned to just accept this.

name: Fanny
description: She has a rare skin condition called vitiligo, causing her hair to depigment.

name: Lewis
description: He’s had health insurance with @Trupanion since he was a puppy. Wanted to help everyone understand exactly how it works, so he helped write an article about it below.

name: Grendel
description: He was wondering if you’d like a strawberry. He has extras so it’s really no pawblem.

name: Koda
description: She was hit by a car last week. Had some internal bleeding, but is doing much better now. Only a little pupset she can’t play while she heals. We’ve covered the remaining cost of her care. Please consider getting pet health insurance. It’s best to be puppared.

name: Chloe
description: She has a degenerative disease called Laryngeal Paralysis Polyneuropothy. A tie-back surgery last year gave her a lot of comfort, but some regurgitation issues have returned. You can read her story and help her afford treatment below.

name: Paul
description: He’s a retired racing greyhound from Florida. Just moved to Philly with his new family and is still adjusting to the concept of winter.

name: Lucy Lu
description: She was denied the opportunity to present her case against bath time. A true injustice.

name: Pearl
description: She can hear a caterpillar hiccup from over a mile away. Happens more than you’d think.

name: Gen, the happiest corgi in the world
description: He’s been blessing us with his facial expressions for years, and it’s about time we honor his magnificence.

name: Kiba
description: He just turned 2, and in his first couple years he’s had a few health scares. Thankfully, his healthcare is covered by @Trupanion, so he can go on all his snowy adventures with peace of mind.

name: Wilber
description: He’s the new sheruff in town. Even has a badge to prove it. Will not be enforcing any laws, only wanted the job for the hat.

name: Stella
description: She just unlocked a new fear: inside squirrels. Not sure why nobody else is concerned.

name: Bear
description: His house is between a baseball field and some tennis courts. He brings a few abandoned balls home every day. After rigorous quality control he takes them all to the dog park for others to play with. Then he starts his collection anew.

name: Cherry
description: She broke her leg chasing a rabbit last weekend. Claims the rabbit started it and she was simply defending her honor. We’ve covered the remaining cost of her surgery. Do us a favor and consider getting pet health insurance. It’s best to be puppared.

name: Smidgen
description: She was rescued from a backyard breeder. During her first vet visit, an echocardiogram revealed two heart conditions. Either could send her into cardiac arrest at any moment. You can help her get the surgery to fix them both below.

name: Biscotti
description: He had a very good day. Exited GME at $360 and will continue to ride AMC to the h*ckin moon.

name: Leia
description: She turned a squeaker toy into a nose flute and would like to play a few notes for you. She’s still learning so please be nice.

name: Tucker
description: He’s the world’s leading snow taster. Seen here making sure this snow is pup to par.

name: Pinky
description: She was diagnosed with lymphoma cancer last year, but was in total remission after her first round of chemo. Sadly, only a few healthy months later, the cancer is back. She’s bravely going to fight it again and you can help her below.

name: Maggie
description: She’s not sure what your fortune says, but if it’s a good one she really hopes it comes true.

name: Aspen
description: She’s visiting a friend’s house for dinner, but after seeing the rug she thinks it’s time to leave.

name: Enzo
description: His bed got a new squeaker feature. Must’ve come with the latest pupdate.

name: Max
description: He was born with a deformity of his paw, making his front right leg shorter than the rest. Surgery is his best option for a pain-free life. He wants to be the best service pup he can be for his human, and you can help him do that below.

name: Oliver
description: He was given a very little ice cream cone today, which is okay because he is also very little.

name: Bishop
description: He stops by occasionally to ask again if you’d like to invest in his craft brewery. He just needs a little boost to get started.

name: Wallace and Charlie
description: They met today in puppy class. Both were nervous about making friends but not anymore.

name: Henley
description: Her lucky hat keeps shrinking. It used to fit so well. If anybody knows what could be causing this please let her know.

name: Millie
description: She was rescued a few months back, and I think it’s safe to say she’s grateful for her new home.

name: Ginsburg
description: One night a few weeks ago she collapsed in pain. A herniated disc had paralyzed her back legs. She still has no feeling after spinal surgery, but as you can see, she hasn’t given up. You can help Ginsy continue her recovery below.

name: Ace
description: He attempted stairs today. Did very well but still feels like there’s room for improvement.

name: Albus
description: He’s only been around for a little bit of 2020, but you... you made it through the whole h*ckin thing.

name: Savage
description: Whenever his legs are struggling in the snow, he simply activates his ears.

name: Hank
description: He was one of our favorite replies to the festive thread yesterday. Claims he tied the tie himself. Even met some friends.

name: Buffy
description: She surprised me when I dropped off the check at @bestfriends yesterday. In total, you all helped us raise over $100,000 by sharing your festive pups.

name: Peety
description: He likes to visit this rainbow bench on his weekend walks. Today there was also a rainbow on his way home.

name: Cake
description: He’s an ice skating legend. Saw this branch back there and couldn’t just leave it.

name: Brewski
description: He’s a professional picnic planner and the new face of @budweiserusa’s holiday can.

name: Happy
description: She found a really good stick. Wanted everybody to see it.

name: Sophie
description: She’s a certified hardwood floor traction tester. Not much traction here.

name: Riley
description: He recently developed a little dip in his noggin. Further tests eventually revealed lymphatic cancer. He’s now hospitalized awaiting treatment, and missing his younger brother Gunner. You can help Riley come home by clicking below.

name: Julio
description: He did not steal a sock. And if he did, it was an accident.

name: Boo Bear
description: He’s not sure what you’re staring at, but he’s glad it’s making you smile.
